cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY

This paper presents a method for localizing contact with high accuracy over curved, 3-D surfaces using a volume of soft material embedded with individual pressure sensors. The focus is on robotic manipulation, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The method involves data-driven techniques for mapping raw signals from pressure sensors to known surface locations and indentation depths, which involves machine learning (cs.CV, cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of a finite-element model for improving the placement of pressure sensors, which involves computational methods (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for deploying tactile sensing capabilities over 3-D surfaces such as a robotic finger or palm, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
